Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.21,0:00:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was that really true, what you said before?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.61,0:01:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's definitely what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.70,0:01:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.05,0:02:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suwa, about those three suspects assigned to Yoshioka,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.10,0:02:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's particularly likely one's an accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.77,0:02:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something on my face?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.12,0:02:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what the heck is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. Ha-ha. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I keep seeing people whispering in secret. Is something going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.92,0:02:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.05,0:02:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.85,0:02:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. N-Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha, it's nothing. There's nothing going on. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.23,0:02:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha-ha, nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.32,0:03:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.54,0:03:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've finished examining the suspect in the Haido City case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.09,0:03:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.51,0:03:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, regarding that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I've outdone myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.68,0:03:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm amazing, don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, really. I really need to brag about my examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.98,0:03:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like the feeling after you've eaten some\Nkatsudon while watching a drama that just came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.24,0:03:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,TAKAGI!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't give us "What is it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:03:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, we want you to tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.92,0:04:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.72,0:04:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, there are others here who's hearts are ready, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.35,0:04:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hearts ready? Hearts ready for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.48,0:04:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-T-Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.06,0:04:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now. So, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.15,0:04:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's... yours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about Inspector Megure's phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.70,0:04:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, that's very funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.49,0:04:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.00,0:04:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See it shining there on Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.05,0:04:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ring. The ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.72,0:04:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.60,0:04:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A ring?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.53,0:05:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've never seen that ring before. And what's\Nmore, it's on the ring finger of her left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could have given her that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. Calm down. Remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.33,0:05:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep your cool. Keep your cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go and ask Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. About that ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I found someone I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.93,0:05:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.60,0:05:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.31,0:05:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh-hah-hah. Just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it's on the ring finger of the left hand that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.19,0:05:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what it means, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.78,0:05:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What it means is what I want to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.82,0:05:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? That ring? It isn't yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.45,0:05:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't buy it; never seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:05:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then, who the heck did?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.27,0:06:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be a patrolman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it was a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hold on for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Quiet down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must be missing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.99,0:06:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Someone is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.30,0:06:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. I'll be there soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:06:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's trouble at a villa in Okutama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.85,0:07:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.73,0:07:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, please take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem. Now about what we were discussing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.32,0:07:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here there's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one step to a glorious future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having your heart ready is OK, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:35.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the light flashes off the ring on Detective Sato's\Nleft hand, will Detective Takagi make a decision at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.64,0:07:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brain of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:33.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a magnificent ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.17,0:09:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sure is an amazing number of gemstones.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they all diamonds?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.26,0:09:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This the first time I've ever seen anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.60,0:09:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a ring I had made to commemorate the debut of my 100th work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.90,0:09:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had "100th" engraved on the reverse side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.07,0:09:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:59.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The truth is I had ordered 100 diamonds to be affixed, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.78,0:10:02.95,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Moroguchi Masataka (52)\NMystery Author
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:04.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If I did that, the size of the ring would be too large, and I was against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, excuse me. I need to change the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.88,0:10:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it unusual to be using a cassette tape recorder nowadays?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:26.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's generally all digital recording now, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:28.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Dejima Kakuji (34)\NWriter
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:31.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm just not happy unless I can see the tape spinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.65,0:10:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm scared of errors with digital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In truth, I'm the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.24,0:10:45.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All of my fellow cameraman are using digital cameras, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:47.66,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tarumi Wataru (33)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.12,0:10:51.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I've been using this analog guy for so long I just can't let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.38,0:10:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well if I can't finish this up soon, I'll be in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.34,0:11:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, I'm sorry to interrupt the pile of analog stories, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:09.73,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Anabuki Harue (33)\NMagazine Editor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.43,0:11:09.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The deadline for Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s on-going serialization is getting close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.52,0:11:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're done with the useless chatter, can you finish what you came to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.65,0:11:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so grumpy, Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The official conversation between me and\NDetective Mouri isn't until tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:31.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This evening we'll feast on my home cooking, and after\Na good rest, we'll do it in the morning sunlight tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.79,0:11:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Writer{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.83,0:11:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like an introductory rehearsal meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.68,0:11:47.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's even on the announcement page in this\Nmonth's edition. Look, the author Moroguchi Masataka...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.01,0:11:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaks with great detective Mouri Kogoro on\Nthe new dawn of mysteries. There's a lot of publicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.69,0:11:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? What's with that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.66,0:12:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just thinking he's kind of different from what I imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Different? You mean Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.33,0:12:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the sensei's mysteries pay excessive attention to minute details.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought for sure he would be an easily irritable and highly strung person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.43,0:12:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.81,0:12:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have a ruler?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. I do happen to have a measuring tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.99,0:12:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When compared to the other authors, the\Ncharacters of my name are one millimeter smaller!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.66,0:12:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make a fool of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.83,0:13:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Not at all. It was just the way the size of the characters came out properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case then make characters of the other author's names smaller!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.76,0:13:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a piece of crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.31,0:13:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.27,0:13:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.90,0:13:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.31,0:13:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that area he's pretty high strung.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really! My chief editor before you, Akiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.53,0:13:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would grant me anything I desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! He sounds like an excellent editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When searching for a file photo or when\Ninvestigating or collecting specialized knowledge regarding a trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would exhaust his flesh and bones without sparing for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until even his very life was exhausted...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.94,0:13:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. In the spring of this year his body was found in his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With all the locks locked, in the middle of a sealed room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A sealed room? Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.99,0:14:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had to be, right? It wasn't one of my mysteries after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.62,0:14:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is I thought I would write a book based on his death, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.55,0:14:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was stopped by Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.30,0:14:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course! His sudden death was well-known in the publication industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.47,0:14:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a novel like that were published,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured it would lead to a bunch of gossip articles on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gossip is just gossip. It's not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides if it was called a memorial of sorts to my editor Akiba,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.86,0:14:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,don't you think, on the contrary, it would be a hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.07,0:14:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.62,0:14:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap, I'm out of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.67,0:15:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you use mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.94,0:15:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to say this is something I use a lot, a pencil. Even though it's analog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.15,0:15:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll use it proudly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.40,0:15:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, for now, since tomorrow's plans have been decided,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.24,0:15:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the production will be tomorrow morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.21,0:15:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd better wrap these up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.38,0:15:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I don't waste the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.31,0:16:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, we continued the program\Nplanning for two more hours, only breaking for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.73,0:16:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we had only known all that work would be useless...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.28,0:16:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, because, the single main participant in those plans was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.62,0:16:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already five o'clock in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.13,0:16:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.75,0:16:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he still sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.51,0:16:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah, it's possible he was up late last night working.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.56,0:16:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let's use the master key and wake him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.22,0:16:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, the sensei really hates it\Nwhen other people come into his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.23,0:16:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there isn't a master key. It seems he stole it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling. A sensation like a\Nstrangling in my chest, suffocating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.33,0:17:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like it always does at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.55,0:17:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd say the time of death was about an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.63,0:17:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An almond odor. Cyanide poisoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.14,0:17:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a coffee stain around his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he drink it with the coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.19,0:17:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the locks in the room are secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only way in was what I used when I came in, a\Nventilation window that only a child could get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.45,0:17:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And probably what's in his hand is the key to this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.54,0:17:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased is the mystery author, Moroguchi Masataka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 52 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death is suffocation from the ingestion of cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from the coffee stains around his mouth, most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He either mixed the cyanide in his coffee and\Ndrank it or was forced to drink it, but which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say he was forced to drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.70,0:18:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door and windows in this room\Nsecurely locked, so it was definitely a sealed room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s holding the key\Nto this room in his hand, and there are no spare keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.17,0:18:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it must be suicide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.01,0:18:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How come? Someone could have\Nplaced cyanide on his coffee cup beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so a crime in this sealed room is still possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course they would have to know that\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drinks coffee when he wakes up in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.07,0:19:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! People don't normally drink coffee while holding keys, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, of course, it would be completely unreasonable to\Ngrab it right after realizing that the coffee had been poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was probably holding that key before\Ndrinking the poison as some kind of message.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was scheduled to have an\Ninterview with you this morning, wasn't he, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe because he overslept he grabbed the key in haste and\Njust before leaving the room he drank the coffee to wake himself up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.85,0:19:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! Look more carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The coffee cup is lying right next to the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:46.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the coffee maker is in the kitchen over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was in a rush, he would have drank\Nthe coffee in the kitchen where he got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't have bothered to place it on a\Nsaucer and bring it over to the bed to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.84,0:19:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, did you think about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone came to wake up Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} this\Nmorning, poured him a cup of coffee and mixed in the cyanide,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and brought it over to his bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.68,0:20:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asking him to be quick, they handed him the key and left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.73,0:20:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.56,0:20:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was the case, then whoever it was would have had\Nto leave the room before Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drank the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.82,0:20:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to get Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's up to the person whether they drink the coffee right away or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.54,0:20:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since he was being pressured he probably drank it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.62,0:20:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But maybe Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has a sensitive tongue\Nand couldn't drink it right away because it was too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.80,0:20:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.59,0:20:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} absolutely loved coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot or lukewarm, he always said it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a well known fact in the editorial department.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.69,0:21:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you guys are?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm the editor in charge of Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, Anabuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.95,0:21:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the two behind me, on the right is the cameraman, Tarumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the left is the writer, Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.58,0:21:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the three of you came here this morning\Nto Moroguchi's villa for the planned interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.67,0:21:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, all three of us spent the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.80,0:21:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would sure be rough to come here by five in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.14,0:21:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it's strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.02,0:21:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this room was sealed, you would have had to\Nbreak down the door or smash a window to get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no sign of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how did you get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.23,0:21:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.99,0:21:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This brat did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} came in through the ventilation\Nwindow and unlocked the door from the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.87,0:22:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we could get into the room also.\NAnd then we found Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that window was open?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.63,0:22:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.51,0:22:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like it's only wide enough for a child to squeeze through.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.35,0:22:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, if this was a suicide, then how come\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was holding the key when he died?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.56,0:22:25.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well it could be that he didn't want any\Nof us in the villa to be suspected of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.44,0:22:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And like I said a second ago if this was a murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.20,0:22:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then unless the murderer said, "Close the door\Nand drink the coffee while holding the key" to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.08,0:22:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to create this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.70,0:22:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, any idea why Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.63,0:22:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.04,0:22:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't seem that type at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.96,0:22:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.26,0:22:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he could have had troubles that he didn't discuss with certain people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.93,0:22:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems his previous chief editor, Akiba,\Ncommitted suicide in the spring of this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.02,0:23:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he might have felt responsible for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.07,0:23:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well anyway, let's wait for forensics to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.28,0:23:16.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this was murder, then the culprit's\Nfingerprints should have been left around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.25,0:23:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if the culprit had poured the coffee or\Nopened and closed the door while wearing gloves,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.42,0:23:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would have become suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.71,0:23:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was no chance to wipe them off after the room is locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's only if you guys didn't touch anything before we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.93,0:23:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't Detective Mouri warned us not to go in until the police arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.98,0:23:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already decided it was suicide. There's no reason to call forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.48,0:23:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.11,0:23:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.28,0:23:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.99,0:23:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The R-l-N-G.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.91,0:23:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.16,0:24:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'd be lying if I said it didn't bother me,\Nbut we're in the middle of an investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.00,0:24:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.42,0:24:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you looking? It's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.30,0:24:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man's ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.51,0:24:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The word "100th" is upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.39,0:24:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right. But maybe he just put in on wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this man was really neurotic, I don't think he'd make a mistake like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.28,0:24:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also this ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.07,0:24:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? It has so many diamonds on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.83,0:24:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's it! This really was a murder after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.25,0:24:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive for the murder was this ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.92,0:24:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After killing Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the culprit switched the real ring with\Na fake ring; but, in a rush, ended up putting it on the opposite way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.01,0:25:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never take off his ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.23,0:25:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right. He was really fond of it. He\Nalways kept it on even while taking a bath or when in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.03,0:25:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's like Detective Takagi says, then the\Npossibility of this being a murder has gotten stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.12,0:25:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more puzzle has arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.37,0:25:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The culprit could have have only\Nswitched the rings after Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.96,0:25:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the culprit must have still been in the room at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.92,0:25:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then how did the culprit escape from this locked room?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.18,0:25:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did they get the key into Mogoguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.52,0:25:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe after poisoning Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the\Nkiller took the key and left the room, locking the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.02,0:25:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they somehow managed to find a way to\Nreturn the key to Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.95,0:26:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing that was open was that ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.24,0:26:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about four meters from there to the corpse's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.21,0:26:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that much distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.13,0:26:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something like that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.93,0:26:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, while we wait for forensics to show up, let's hear from you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.43,0:26:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you and what were you\Ndoing before Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.52,0:26:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First up is Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.48,0:26:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I was fixing this tape recorder in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.49,0:26:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't working very well. The tape inside got\Nmessed up and when I tried to rewind it, it made this sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.87,0:26:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That sure is a strange sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.29,0:26:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is Tarumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.38,0:26:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After I finished setting up my photography stuff, I was\Nalso in my room organizing the negatives for some other work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.63,0:27:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using these rubber bands to tie them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.64,0:27:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Then, next is Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.51,0:27:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in my room as well checking the galleys for other authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.02,0:27:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Auntie. You had a metal tape\Nmeasure, didn't you? Do you always carry that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.69,0:27:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Because the sensei always asks me\Nto measure things, like the size of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.03,0:27:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's just to measure words then why not a ruler?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.66,0:27:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, boy. It's not just used for\Nwords, you can measure lots of stuff with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.96,0:27:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a door or a window that can be used for a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.76,0:27:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know a lot about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.26,0:27:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We learned a lot from Akiba before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.93,0:27:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he and the three of us joined the company the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.35,0:27:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I ended up quitting and became a freelance writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.39,0:27:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.77,0:27:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Uhm, Detective Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.15,0:28:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't related to the case, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.57,0:28:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.37,0:28:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.41,0:28:09.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. Later, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.42,0:28:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.67,0:28:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? It's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.00,0:28:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ring is genuine?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.72,0:28:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.84,0:28:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we took it to the station right away and had\Nan expert take a look at it, so we're positive it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.26,0:28:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I guess the culprit's motive wasn't the ring after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.14,0:28:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.40,0:28:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why? What reason did the culprit have for taking the ring off?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.36,0:28:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, come to think of it, when we took the ring off we found a strange mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.11,0:28:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strange mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.57,0:28:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.49,0:28:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It faded a lot, but there's a blackened circle around this finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.04,0:28:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.00,0:29:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blood? Why is there blood there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.05,0:29:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he cut himself while shaving and he touched the cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.97,0:29:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.97,0:29:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? There's a cut under his right jaw. There's no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.85,0:29:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, on the coffee cup, this saucer,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.77,0:29:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the coffee maker or on the doorknob there\Nwere no prints other than those of the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.99,0:29:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.70,0:29:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Uhm, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.41,0:29:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.00,0:29:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This may be inappropriate at a time like this, but I really wanted to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.21,0:29:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.42,0:29:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Congratulations on your engagement!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.93,0:29:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.22,0:29:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, look! The ring that Detective Sato has on he\Nleft hand ring finger, that's an engagement ring, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.40,0:29:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.56,0:30:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Looks like it?" Are you saying you didn't give it to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.11,0:30:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope. It's someone else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.03,0:30:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she's replaced you with a more reliable and good looking guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.78,0:30:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.37,0:30:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.87,0:30:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You suppose so? Shouldn't you find out for sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.84,0:30:25.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be nice if I could, but I'm kind of scared of the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.88,0:30:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously. It's like having to walk a tightrope.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.80,0:30:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you haven't fallen off the rope already?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.56,0:30:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.81,0:30:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, Dad, stop teasing him!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.81,0:30:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! So that's why!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.23,0:30:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the culprit took the ring off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.86,0:30:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to make sure the "tightrope\Nwalk" in the sealed room would be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.07,0:30:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still don't quite get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.91,0:30:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door and the windows in the room were locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.29,0:31:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased, Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, died\Nfrom drinking coffee poisoned with cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.42,0:31:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his left hand was the one and only key to the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.38,0:31:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only opening was a ventilation\Nwindow that a child could barely get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.26,0:31:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just from this it looks like he killed himself and didn't\Nwant anybody else in the villa to be suspected of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.02,0:31:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is that the ring on the middle finger of his left\Nhand that was holding the key, was placed on upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.86,0:31:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to this woman, Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} almost never took his ring off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.33,0:31:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since he's not the type who would put it on wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.21,0:31:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then after someone poisoned\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, for some reason they took the ring off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.80,0:31:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when putting it back on they accidentally put it on upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.88,0:31:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they took the ring off because there was blood on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.22,0:32:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, there was blood under the ring\Nfrom when he cut himself shaving, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.98,0:32:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe the culprit took the ring off his finger to wipe the blood off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.61,0:32:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, if that was the case, then they\Nwould have wiped the blood off his finger too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.86,0:32:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if they wiped the blood off the ring, it'd be\Nmeaningless if there was still blood on the finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.29,0:32:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the culprit wiped the blood without taking the ring off?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.87,0:32:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.37,0:32:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe that guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.67,0:32:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was sewing?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.30,0:32:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sewing? What do you mean, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.34,0:32:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I mean... Remember? Earlier when you were making me the\Ndust cloth I take to school, you were wearing a ring, right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.31,0:32:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Oh, you mean the thimble?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.73,0:32:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you have that on it's easier to\Npass the thread through the needle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.28,0:32:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's wrong! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, a thimble is used in order to push on the needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.53,0:33:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? I thought for sure that they used that\Nring to push something through the hole in the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.04,0:33:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh well, I was just wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.72,0:33:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put something through the hole in the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.64,0:33:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why the ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.74,0:33:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.36,0:33:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.11,0:33:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rubber bands!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.03,0:33:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rubber bands?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.62,0:33:48.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First you chain the rubber bands together, then you pass the\Nbands through the ring and create something like a slingshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.54,0:33:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hook the top and bottom of the key on both ends of the rubber\Nbands and you fling it into the room through the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.18,0:34:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can control the length of the rubber bands by how many you attach.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.10,0:34:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And of course this was done after poisoning\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and leaving the room with the door locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.27,0:34:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only person who could have done this is the\Nperson who is still wearing tons of rubber bands on his wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.86,0:34:18.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cameraman, Tarumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.16,0:34:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.62,0:34:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.12,0:34:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrong again, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.46,0:34:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if that was the case, shouldn't the rubber bands still be in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.21,0:34:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're flinging them into the room along with the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.13,0:34:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then he only used one side.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.09,0:34:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He held one end of the rubber bands\Nand hung the key on the other end to fling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.64,0:34:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way he just has to pull on the end\Nhe was holding to be able to get it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.44,0:34:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if he was able to get them back that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.77,0:34:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the knots in the rubber bands would get caught in the\Nring and pull, making the corpse's arm dangle from the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.16,0:35:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, would the culprit really choose an impossible task\Nlike flinging a key into the palm of a hand with rubber bands?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.33,0:35:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it failed, people would think the key was\Njust thrown in through the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.79,0:35:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.46,0:35:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.17,0:35:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, I could put him to sleep and\Nperform the deduction show like always, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.35,0:35:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Sato is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.47,0:35:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came close to finding out once already.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.81,0:35:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll have to just lead them into realizing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.44,0:35:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're right, Uncle. I don't think even the\Npeople at the circus can do a trick like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.91,0:35:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The circus? Are you talking about magicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.29,0:35:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Detective Takagi was saying that he\Nwas walking a tightrope with Detective Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.13,0:35:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the two of them are doing a circus trick, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.13,0:36:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aah, w-wait, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.01,0:36:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you mean, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.05,0:36:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what was mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.26,0:36:09.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, walking a\Ntightrope. Walking a tightrope.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.47,0:36:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, there is one thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.02,0:36:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something long and narrow that won't get\Ncaught in the ring and you can get back right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.82,0:36:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you finally figured it out, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.36,0:36:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the editor, carries...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.03,0:36:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The metal tape measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.54,0:36:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.54,0:36:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she put the measuring tape through the ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.87,0:36:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she just hooked the tip of the measuring tape on the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.50,0:36:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she put the measuring tape through the hole in the key and\Nsent it from outside the ventilation window into Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.05,0:36:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like a tightrope walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.85,0:36:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a sec. When did she put the\Nmeasuring tape through the hole in the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.39,0:36:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did it immediately after poisoning Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.69,0:37:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key went on the measuring tape first, then she hooked the tip\Nonto the ring, and then stretched it out to the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.36,0:37:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the body of the tape measure along\Nwith the key is hooked on the window edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.53,0:37:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then, afterwards, she just has to lift it up from the window and the\Nkey will follow the measuring tape right into Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.33,0:37:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, of course, you can get it back with just one button.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.67,0:37:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I meant was, how do you lock the door if the key\Nwas already on the tape measure before you left the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.76,0:37:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.02,0:37:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe she stretched out the measuring tape after\Ncommitting the crime and leaving the room with the door locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.86,0:37:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she did it after going outside to the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.82,0:37:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You know, since it's a rigid metal\Ntape measure, you could use it like a stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.11,0:37:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you cleverly get the tip of the tape\Nmeasure to the corpse on the bed and hook it on the ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.54,0:37:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can only be done up to one meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.75,0:37:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything longer than that and it'll bend before\Neven reaching either the palm of the hand or the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.38,0:38:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides, what's the point of taking the\Nring off if you just need to hook something on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.67,0:38:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-True.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.01,0:38:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If only there was something long and thin like a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.43,0:38:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But none of the three suspects had anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.19,0:38:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked around the villa and there's\Nbeen no report of anything like that being found.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.03,0:38:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.36,0:38:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike a rubber band, it would have to be something that wouldn't\Nget caught in the ring and was thin, smooth and long like a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.91,0:38:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus you'd have to always be able to wrap it up like a\Ntape measure. There can't be anything that convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.58,0:38:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.54,0:38:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Could that be a...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.71,0:38:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ca—
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.54,0:38:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cassette Tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.26,0:38:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see, using a cassette tape you can\Npull out the tape and put it through the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.60,0:38:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And pull the end of the tape back to where the\Ncassette is placed outside the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.56,0:39:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way after you poison Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nyou lock the door and leave the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.94,0:39:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from outside the ventilation window you put\Nthe tape you left there through the hole in the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.90,0:39:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just by lifting the tape up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.40,0:39:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key will slide down the tape due to\Ngravity and arrive on the corpse's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.16,0:39:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, if you wind up the tape, it'll slip through the key and the\Nring and return to the cassette. And so the sealed room is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.88,0:39:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the only person who was able to use this trick\Nis the person who habitually carries a cassette tape around.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.26,0:39:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who wouldn't regarded as\Nsuspicious by the police when examined later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.14,0:39:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.48,0:39:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The writer, Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.98,0:39:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be anyone except you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.23,0:39:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely you said you had some last minute checks for the\Narrangements of the interview that was planned this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.36,0:39:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you asked Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to let you into his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.58,0:40:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then when he wasn't looking you\Nmixed cyanide in his coffee, thus killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.17,0:40:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you used the trick we just discussed making this a sealed room.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.09,0:40:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Are we wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.80,0:40:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we'll know if we just examine the cassette tape you're carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.89,0:40:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to say that the tape will be\Ntwisted, but I told you about that, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.23,0:40:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That this recorder...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.61,0:40:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't working correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.94,0:40:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I have plenty of tapes that are twisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.15,0:40:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus it makes a loud noise whenever it winds\Nsomething up, someone would have heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.79,0:40:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I didn't use this and just quickly reeled in the tape by hand\Nthen a large portion would have been twisted. Go ahead and check.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.67,0:40:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have a tape like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.84,0:40:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.30,0:40:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pencil!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.39,0:41:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stuck the pencil you borrowed from\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} last night into the hole in the cassette to wind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.56,0:41:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way you can wind the tape back in a short amount of\Ntime without using the recorder and without damaging it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.28,0:41:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did it a lot when I was a kid too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.61,0:41:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever I was goofing around and ended up pulling out a lot of\Ntape I had to wind up, I'd put it on my knee and roll it up with a pencil.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.62,0:41:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was talking about examining the\Ntape, it wasn't about whether the tape was twisted or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.30,0:41:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like we said before, there was blood under the ring on his left middle finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.80,0:41:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason there was one place where it was rubbed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.14,0:41:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it should be somewhere on the cassette tape that you're carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.60,0:41:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one you used for the sealed room\Ntightrope walk, a tape with Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.69,0:41:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.44,0:41:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Could it be, because of Akiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.45,0:42:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha, a tightrope walk? Akiba used to say that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.49,0:42:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That his relationship with\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was a continuous tightrope walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.63,0:42:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A tightrope walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.38,0:42:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akiba was a careful sort-of guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.67,0:42:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but ever since he became in charge of the\Nsensei, he was always wearing a bandage somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.97,0:42:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.35,0:42:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the sensei told him to, he was testing them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.77,0:42:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the murder tricks the sensei thought up, he was\Nusing his own body to confirm if they would work or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.48,0:42:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course taking meticulous care to make sure he didn't die for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.11,0:42:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! So the incident where Akiba was found dead in a sealed room was...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.83,0:42:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When I was sorting through the\Neffects in Akiba's desk at the office, I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.79,0:42:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A notebook of tricks in which was\Nwritten the exact same way that Akiba died!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.80,0:42:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't you turn that over to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.34,0:43:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been useless. If put on the spot, the\Nsensei would have just said, "Akiba did that on his own."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.93,0:43:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was still an accident, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.48,0:43:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the sensei said it like this in another interview:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.11,0:43:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this age, I've finally started to understand the murderer's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.61,0:43:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a mystery writer, there's nothing more joyous than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.78,0:43:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he said. And that's when I knew for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.49,0:43:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the sensei wanted to know by making use of Akiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.33,0:43:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the reality of the tricks...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.83,0:43:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But rather the mentality of the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.88,0:45:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? I've been wondering about it for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.01,0:45:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.68,0:45:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't "about what" me. What did you\Nmean about walking on a tightrope with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.94,0:45:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. That was, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.31,0:45:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was your ring! Detective Sato, you always say you dislike shiny things.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.86,0:45:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Detective Takagi was wondering why you're wearing a ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.16,0:45:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's good that she's just as blunt as Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.62,0:45:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this? You mean this charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.58,0:45:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.38,0:45:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.00,0:45:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.17,0:45:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Silver and turquoise.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.47,0:45:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wear one on your left hand ring finger it'll keep the\Nbad bugs away, killing two birds with one stone, Yumi said.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.81,0:45:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm doing it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.77,0:45:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know I'm cursed and I hate bugs, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.81,0:46:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, when Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said bugs she didn't mean those bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.69,0:46:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-In that case, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please wear my ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.20,0:46:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On your left hand ring finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.33,0:46:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.71,0:46:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, I bet she was grilled by everybody today.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.21,0:46:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is wearing my ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.59,0:46:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On her left hand ring finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.76,0:46:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But today I need to act dignified.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.22,0:46:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And face them like a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.02,0:46:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, we heard about it. Sato's ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.48,0:46:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.82,0:46:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.90,0:46:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it was just a charm!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.36,0:46:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on with everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.28,0:46:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.03,0:46:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.45,0:46:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to think that she doesn't know the meaning of the left hand ring finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.37,0:47:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes it even more exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.92,0:47:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I didn't tell her yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.96,0:47:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meaning of that ring. Oh well...
